name: November Meetup - All about Software/Data Carpentries + TidyText Group Activity
description:
We will be in CLSB 1S018 of the OHSU Life Sciences Building on the Waterfront. The classroom is located on the main floor, no need to go up stairs or elevators!

Map:

More info about the location:
http://www.ohsu.edu/xd/about/visiting/directions/clsb-life-sciences.cfm

Agenda (may change):

6:30 - 7:00 - Introductions (maybe share something you've done, learned, or wanted to learn about R this week) + R Ladies Business (see link for discussion items: https://github.com/rladies-pdx/meeting_recaps/wiki/2017-11-30-Agenda )

7:00 - 7:15 - Carpentries Presentation (Augustina)

Augustina is in the final stages of Carpentries Instructor Certification and will do a short presentation on it. For more info see: https://software-carpentry.org (https://software-carpentry.org/)

7:15 - 8:00 - Group Activity! Last month we co-hosted a TidyText tutorial with Julia Silge! Augustina has been doing analysis on Meetup activity for R-Ladies Global. Let's apply the TidyText things to R-Ladies Meetup text content including both group and event descriptions.

Meetup Analysis:
Notebook (WIP): https://rpubs.com/rladiespdx/rladies-meetup-eda
Repo: https://github.com/rladies-pdx/meetup-analysis/
Meetup Data: https://github.com/rladies-pdx/meetup-analysis/tree/master/latest

TidyText Tutorial:
Augustina's R Notebook from our Meetup: https://rpubs.com/auggy/tidytext_ulysses
Book: http://tidytextmining.com/

Do you want to present something? Let us know!

We will also provide FOOD because no one likes to R on an empty stomach :)

Elephant's Deli is conveniently located adjacent to the Meetup Space so food will come from there with Vegetarian + Gluten Free options.

name: Linear, Logistic, and Cox Regression: When and How to Run in RStudio
description:
Join us to learn about regression in RStudio. This month's meet up will be led by Jacqueline Kueper, PhD candidate in Epidemiology and Biostatistics at Western.

No previous experience with regression or RStudio is required; all abilities are welcome. The main portion of the session will involve step-by-step instructions on how to set up, run, and interpret results from regression models that include one and more than one independent variable. We will also cover some background on three types of regression‚Äîlinear, logistic, and Cox‚Äîincluding when and why you might want to run each of these models. Sample code and data will be made available so that you can follow along on a personal laptop; sitting back to absorb the conversation in a more hands-off way is also an option.

Get excited! See you in December!
how_to_find_us: We are in the Wellington Room, on the second floor at the back. Parking under the library (entrance on King St) can be validated for up to 2 hours at the library help desk.

name: Intro to dplyr & ggplot2 with Marieke Jones
description:
* Updated Location * Please note that we will be meeting at Hemoshear, not VividCortex. Hemoshear is located near the other end of the Downtown Mall at 501 Locust Avenue, Suite 301. There is free parking in the parking lot.¬†

Pipes, plots, and more!¬†

Join us for a two-part workshop led by UVA's Marieke Jones on two core packages in the tidyverse: dplyr and ggplot2. This session is geared towards all proficiency levels in R. Whether you've just started learning and you want to know what piping is or how to make a plot, or if you're a pro and you want a refresher on writing cleaner code, this workshop will be beneficial to you. Also, there will be pizza :)

Schedule:

‚Ä¢¬†6:00-6:45 Intro to R

‚Ä¢¬†6:45-7:30 Intro to dplyr¬†

Come to one or both!¬†

Please bring a laptop with R, RStudio, and the tidyverse package installed before coming to the MeetUp. If you need a short tutorial on getting oriented in R and on installing a package in R, please see this YouTube video.¬†We will be available 30min before the session starts to assist anyone with troubles installing R, RStudio, or packages.

Please download the nhanes.csv dataset we will be using during the sessions. Save this file to your Desktop so you can easily find it.¬†

Follow us on twitter for more updates! @RLadiesCville

See you then!

description:
***NOTE: RSVP is on Eventbrite for this event! Here's the link: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/all-the-ladies-in-tech-happy-hour-winter-edition-tickets-39194718458 ***

This is a quarterly mega happy hour / networking mixer with the goal of connecting women in tech, data, and code in ATX.
Apana's is offering a Happy Hour special of $1 off beer or wine. We've reserved their back room and around 7pm, we'll do some quick introductions for all of the groups present and a preview of the events they have planned for the winter.
We're also partnering with Dress for Success Austin to do a drive for shoes and purses at this event -- if you have any extra shoes or purses, please consider bringing them to help women who are in need!
This event is cohosted by these groups (please reach out if you know of a group that would like to co-host with us!):
+ R-Ladies Austin
+ Women in Data Science
+ PyLadies ATX
+ Women Who Code
+ ChickTech Austin
+ Austin Women in Technology
+ Girl Develop It Austin
Feel free to bring guests, but please note that we are limiting this event to those who identify as women only.
Can't wait to see you all there!

name: Pubquiz navide√±o R-Ladies + PyLadies + OSWeekends + HaskellMAD
description:
¬°Buenas, R-Ladies!

Se acerca el √∫ltimo mes del a√±o y con √©l, lo queramos o no, la Navidad, las compras, los viajes, las cenas de empresa y el poco tiempo libre... As√≠ que hemos pensado en hacer del meetup de diciembre un evento m√°s festivo.

Como han hecho en comunidades R-Ladies de otras ciudades, os proponemos un pubquiz (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pub_quiz), que es un concurso en un pub (s√≠, el nombre es muy descriptivo!).

##### Comunidades participantes #####

‚Ä¢ R-Ladies (https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/rladies-madrid/)

‚Ä¢ PyLadies (https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/PyLadiesMadrid/)

‚Ä¢ Open Source Weekends (https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Open-Source-Weekends/)

‚Ä¢ Madrid Haskell Users Group (https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Haskell-MAD/)

##### Funcionamiento #####

##### Equipos #####

Se har√°n equipos (lo m√°s igualados posible en cuesti√≥n de comunidades y tecnolog√≠as, que al menos haya un integrante de cada comunidad).

Cada equipo tiene que tener un nombre (que eligen sus integrantes) y lo ponen en su papel de respuestas.

##### Preguntas y respuestas #####

Las preguntas se dir√°n por megafon√≠a y se contestar√°n en un papel. Los organizadores de cada comunidad llevar√°n preparadas un m√≠nimo de 10 preguntas. Cada pregunta tendr√° una respuesta √∫nica. El tema de las preguntas es tecnolog√≠a (lenguajes, etc.) o preguntas sobre la comunidad.

##### Ganador #####

El equipo con m√°s respuestas correctas es el ganador.

##### Normas #####

No se puede consultar la respuesta por internet. Seamos legales, ¬°vamos a pasarlo bien!

##### Entradas #####

Cada comunidad contar√° con 10 entradas, para que est√©n equilibrados entre los participantes los conocimientos t√©cnicos.

##### Asistencia #####

Por favor, si no te apuntas y luego ves que no vas a poder venir, ¬°libera tu plaza! Por muy poco tiempo que quede para el evento. En este meetup es especialmente importante para que los equipos puedan estar equilibrados. ¬°Gracias!

** Disclaimer: ¬°sinti√©ndolo mucho no contamos con ayuda econ√≥mica as√≠ que cada uno se tendr√° que pagar las consumiciones que tome! ¬°Gracias!

* Getting started with making R packages If there are any topics you'd like to cover or have an interesting talk to give then we'd love to hear from you. name: Kick-starting R-Ladies Vancouver!!!!
description:
Hello R-Ladies community!


We are ready to kick-start our Vancouver chapter of the R-Ladies!


Come along to this introductory event where we will discuss the mission of R-Ladies, goals of our chapter and get to know each other. This event is kindly supported by Hothead Games, who are hosting us at their office downtown, thanks a bunch Hothead Games! Also, shout-out to RStudio for providing the food. Space is limited so please make sure you RSVP to get your spot.


If you haven‚Äôt done so yet, please fill out this survey to help us organize future events: https://goo.gl/forms/oztMH7oj0bcKHFUq1


Here is a tentative agenda. Times may shift depending on how many folks show up and what you are interested in sharing.


¬†6:00-6:15 pm - Arriving/networking


¬†6:15 pm: Introduction; a presentation with a discussion on:

¬†‚Ä¢ What is R-Ladies?

¬†‚Ä¢ What would we like to see at R-Ladies events

¬†‚Ä¢ Share your comments about location for future meetups

¬†‚Ä¢ Any other R-Ladies Vancouver issues you would like to discuss email: vancouver@rladies.org


7:00 pm - Lightning talks or an R related talk (depending on interest)


Lightning talks - this is an opportunity to informally introduce ourselves and share what we are using R for or what we are hoping to do with R (~ 5-10 minutes each). If you would like to give a little talk, here's a link to sign up HERE.There is no need for fancy slides (or any slides), the idea is to share our R interests/backgrounds and for the members to get to know each other.

name: R-Ladies Launch with Hadley Wickham
description:
Hi Everyone!


We are thrilled to announce our meetup launch with Hadley Wickham presenting an introduction to the tidyverse.¬†

This will aimed all all R abilities. For those¬†very new to R or those who have using the tidyverse for a while, you'll still pick up some new tricks.

Bio:¬†
Hadley is Chief Scientist at RStudio, a member of the R Foundation, and Adjunct Professor at Stanford University and the University of Auckland. He builds tools (both computational and cognitive) to make data science easier, faster, and more fun. His work includes packages for data science (the tidyverse: including ggplot2, dplyr, tidyr, purrr, and readr) and principled software development (roxygen2,¬†
testthat, devtools). He is also a writer, educator, and speaker promoting the use of R for data science. Learn more on his website,¬†http://hadley.nz¬†.


This meetup is being run in conjunction with the Data Science Discussion group¬†https://www.meetup.com/Data-Science-Discussion-Auckland/


We look forward to meeting you.

R-Ladies Auckland.

name: Rise & Shiny - Interactive Maps (Leaflet)
description:
December Rise & Shiny will cover topics in Interactive Maps and how to use the Leaflet package/framework in Shiny apps. We're going to try a slightly different format this month: less "lecture" tutorial, and more "choose your own adventure" tutorial. Our goal will be to publish tutorial material on Friday night, before the workshop, so that you can get a sense for what part or sections you might like to try working through on Saturday morning.

Topics of Interest:
- The leaflet package
- R packages for extending leaflet
- GeoJSON (what is it / how to create it)
- Alternatives to leaflet
- Github and shinyapps.io
- Coffee and Muffins!

Thanks as always to our sponsor, B23 - platform.b23.io

This event is open to all members of the RStats community who support our mission of increasing gender diversity in tech. If this is your first meetup with us, please take a moment to read our code of conduct before committing to attend.

name: Communicating Your Data Science Results and Wrangling Data
description:
WHAT WE'RE DOING:

You‚Äôll learn to use R Markdown to communicate your data science results easily. Your end product will be a website (html), Word doc, or a pdf.¬† You‚Äôll also learn to use R package dplyr to wrangle your data; this includes making and/or transforming variables. After the demos, we'll have some time to chat and try out our new skills.

WHAT TO BRING:

Bring your laptop. Your laptop cord and a notebook might be a good idea, too. If you can, try to install R, R Studio, and the dplyr package before coming.

VOLUNTEERS:

Amanda Doan will demonstrate how to use R Markdown and Katie Jolly will teach us how to use dplyr.


CONSUMING THINGS:

Just down the hall is a mini coffee shop. (Bring your own mug to get 25 cents off!) Feel free to bring snackies or beverages from home.

LOCATION:

Meet us in room 226 of O'Shaughnessy Science (OSS). This is connected to Owens and is part of the Frey Science Center (big cement sign out front). OSS is on the west side of Cretin between Grand and Summit. The east side of the building has an elevator and the building is ADA accessible.

PARKING:


You can park on Summit for free. The parking ramp (on Grand and Cretin) is very close to OSS and is decently priced ($1.00 or $1.50 per hour).
how_to_find_us: Room 226 in OSS. OSS is on Cretin between Grand and Summit.

name: Kick-off Meeting
description:
R-Ladies Leuven is now officially alive and kicking! And to celebrate we are organizing our first kick-off meeting to shape the future of¬†our chapter. In this meeting, we will introduce R-Ladies and R-Ladies Leuven, we will get to know each other, and we will discuss how we want to shape future events in our community.¬†


Schedule:

5:30pm - Doors open

5:45pm - Welcome and introduction to R-Ladies and R-Ladies Leuven (who we are!)

6:00pm - Participants introduction (who you are and what you want to get from R-Ladies Leuven)

6:30pm - Discussion and presentation of our December monthly meeting (we have one speaker already confirmed!)


This is our kick-off meeting and want to host it in an informal way to get to know each other. Because of that, we chose Pangaea, where we can meet and discuss while having some drinks and snacks. After the meeting, we can continue the discussion at the nearby STUKcaf√©.

Remember that the stated priority of the R-Ladies communities is the development & support specifically of those identifying as female. However, due to unexpected demand, we have opened learning participation to all genders, provided everybody respects the guidelines of our code of conduct. So feel free to come and join!

Merry Christmas Everyone!

To celebrate the festive season come and join us on December 11 for our annual R-Ladies Christmas Party! There will be R-related games with lots of prizes, drinks and pizza. Come along and get to know your fellow members!

This is also a great opportunity to let us know your thoughts on the meetings we've had this year and what you would like to see next year. If you would like contribute to the group, whether by giving a short talk, workshop or seminar we would love to hear from you.

It's going to be a great night and we hope to see everyone there!

Please remember to bring a laptop with you.

Wishing you all a safe and happy holiday.

R-Ladies Melbourne

name: R in the world of Education
description:
We are very excited to announce our last meetup of the year with Erin Grand.

Her Talk:¬†Many schools across the country are starting to use data to help improve student outcomes. In this talk,¬†Erin¬†will discuss what kind of data she gets to dive into and some of the challenges each project faces. She'll talk about ways to clean messy data, how using R has helped speed up everything, and the amazing janitor package.

Her Bio: ¬†Erin¬†joined Uncommon Schools as an Associate Director of Data Analytics in the summer of 2016. Prior to Uncommon, she worked as a Data¬†Scientist at Crisis Text Line and a software programmer at NASA. She recently completed her masters¬†in Data Science at Columbia University. In the past,¬†Erin¬†researched star formation and taught introductory courses in astronomy and physics. In her free time,¬†Erin¬†enjoys reading, dancing and singing loudly to musical theatre.

Agenda:¬†

6:30-6:45pm Light networking

6:45-7:00pm R-Ladies New York Announcements

7:00-7:45pm R in the world of Education by Erin Grand with Q&A

7:45-8:30pm End of year celebration/networking for R-ladies NewYork.

We want to thank our very generous host,¬†AT&T NYC Data Science Research Center(stats.research.att.com) for having us in their space.¬†

name: Intro to R Markdown + Collaborative Coding Activity w/Kaylene McClanahan
description:
At this meetup, Kaylene McClanahan will lead us through our first collaborative coding activity! Kaylene will briefly introduce us to R Markdown (a great tool for easily annotating your code, sharing it with others, and turning your results into reports), and then we will work together in small groups to address a highly important and socially relevant question--where can you find NYC's most raging parties?

We know the idea of coding with others can be daunting, but this is a safe space and everyone is welcome (even if you do not know how to use R yet). In fact, each group will be assigned a more experienced R user so this will be a great opportunity for beginners to see how other people deal with data in R! This will be a relaxed environment and a good chance to meet some of your fellow R Ladies, so please do not feel like you do not know enough to join in.

If you can, bring your computer!

Schedule:
6:00-6:10--Food and introductions
6:10-6:30--Brief explanation of R Markdown and introduction to the NYC party dataset
6:30-7:20--Groups will explore the data and use R Markdown to document their process/results
7:20-7:45--Groups will share what they did with the rest of the group (if they want to!)

name: New year, new R meetup!
description:
Ring in the new year with a resolution to use R more!

Who are we? We are a few women in Philadelphia who use R and wanted to have a friendly community to extend our R skills and network with other women R users. We learned about the international R-Ladies community and decided to try it in our city.

Anyone with an interest in R is welcome. You can be an R expert or novice.

When? This January will be the first meeting. We plan to have an informal mixer to introduce ourselves and find out what topics are of the most interest for future meetings. After this first meeting, we hope to start a monthly schedule of interactive workshops led by volunteers. If you have anything you want to share, a problem you are working on, or an idea for a collaborative project, we want to hear about it!

If you are completely new to R, bring your computer, and we can walk you through setting up R and RStudio or answer any setup questions you have been working through.

Where? We are being hosted at MakeOffices in center city. There will be snacks (details TBD)

description: Come join the R-Ladies in our first "Lightening Talks" event. In this fun, informal setting, participants have approximately 3 to 5 minutes to speak about their research, work, or a puzzle they're trying to solve - anything goes as long as it involves R! Prepare a brief presentation and a visual or two (slide, code snippets, graph, etc). Come share your work, learn what your peers are up to, and exchange ideas! If you would like to present, fill out our questionnaire before December 23, if you would like to attend please RSVP at our MeetUp page by January 23. Thanks!

name: Lightening Talks
description:
Come join the R-Ladies in our first ever Lightening Talks event. In this fun, informal setting, participants have approximately 3 to 5 minutes to speak about their research, work, or a puzzle they're trying to solve - anything goes! R-related presentations are a bonus but not necessary! Our goal is to 1) provide a space to learn about the others in our community and 2) exchange ideas about methodologies, interests, and the tools we all are using.

IMPORTANT:

In addition to RSVPing on our MeetUp page, please ALSO complete this form by December 23 to help us with scheduling and to let us know important pieces of information.

This is not meant to be a high-stakes presentation event - just a chance to share our projects with each other and learn a little about the questions each of us are asking in our own work and the tools we're using to answer them. As usual, we will head out for food and drinks following the event (drinks and apps for presenters are on us!)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NB: Please note that, in keeping with the global R-Ladies mission, R-Ladies London, Ontario will prioritize female leadership and participation. All interested people (regardless of gender) are welcome to RSVP to our events. However, in the event that we receive a greater amount of presenter interest than we feel is manageable for the space/time, we will prioritize female presenters.
